          "lecture_id": "numerical_root_finding_001",
          "span": "A root-finding problem asks for a value \\(x^*\\) at which a scalar function is zero:\n\n\\[\nf(x^*) = 0.\n\\]\n\nNewton's method uses the derivative to replace the function locally by its tangent line. Provided \\(f'(x_k)\\neq 0\\), its update is\n\n\\[\nx_{k+1} = x_k - \\frac{f(x_k)}{f'(x_k)}.\n\\]"
        }
      ],
      "rationale": "The Newton update formula provides the iterative update rule that defines how Newton's method solves the root-finding problem, thus formalizing the problem's solution condition."
    }
  ]
